article.headline: Lehigh 80, Monmouth, N.J. 71
article.story: WEST LONG BRANCH, N.J. -- Marquis Hall scored 23 points as Lehigh held on for an 80-71 win over Monmouth on Sunday. Phil Anderson added 16 points and Rob Keefer had 15 for the Mountain Hawks (7-3), who never trailed and led by as many as 30 points in the first half. However, Monmouth (2-12) fought back and eventually cut the lead to 69-62 on George Barbour's layup with 2:18 left to play, but Lehigh then made 9-of-11 free throws in the final minute to seal the win. Yaniv Simpson led the Hawks with 25 points -- including six 3-pointers -- and seven rebounds. Barbour came off the bench to score 13 points, while Mike Myers Keitt finished with 12. Lehigh won the battle of the boards, outrebounding Monmouth 43-34.
